I rummaged about with my hand in this box in order to make noises that will be used in the rhythm section of a number of songs I’m working on. They are recorded with a Leem SR-105 dynamic microphone through an Edirol UA-25 directly on my computer. Such samples are very usable to create non-standard rhythm patterns, e.g. by looping them or by by putting them randomly in a song. These samples are the non-processed ones (even no noise reduction) in order to give you maximum freedom to manipulate the original recordings.

693863.title: CRT TV Whine
693863.description:
The high-pitched, incessant whine a CRT television makes while on. Small ticks can also be heard as the TV warms up. Meant to be played at a low volume; the audio was boosted here for editing purposes, but it was recorded at -36 dB. The television in question is a small 14 inch PAL set, so it produces a 15,625 Hz frequency. This is audible to young people, but if you are older than about 20-30, you won't hear a whine.  Recorded 07/07/2023 on H4n Pro.
Edited in Audacity.

169636.title: 45-Little Minolta 35mm-Film Load-takeSomeShots(48000 Hz).mp3
169636.description:
Sounds from a little Minolta camera,was a test i done.
In that sound , i load the film, closed the back door. The camera loads film in a initial position automatically. So i did some shots to record that sound of motor drive pulling the film. 
Was recorded in a Fostex MR8HD, with a pair of large diafragm microphone , made by me. 
---------------
Sons de uma pequena camera Minolta motorizada . Usei um filme velado . No som carrego o films , fecho a tampo trazeira, ela puxa o filme automaticamente, e eu tiro algumas fotos , pra gravar o som do mecanismo puxando o filme .Gravado com um par de microfones , de diafragma grande , feitos por mim , ligados a um Fostex MR8HD digital.
